Piwik::API(3)         User Contributed Perl Documentation        Piwik::API(3)



[1mNAME[0m
       Piwik::API - Use the piwik API

[1mVERSION[0m
       Version 0.02

[1mSYNOPSIS[0m
       Add/Delete and list users and sites from user piwik

       Perhaps a little code snippet.

           use Piwik::API;

           my $foo = Piwik::API->new();
           ...

[1mSUBROUTINES/METHODS[0m
   [1madd_site[0m
           addSite

   [1mdelete_site[0m
           deleteSite

   [1mlist_sites[0m
           getAllSitesId

   [1mget_site_code[0m
           SitesManager.getJavascriptTag

   [1mget_site[0m
           SitesManager.getSiteFromId

   [1madd_user[0m
           addUser

   [1mdelete_user[0m
           deleteUser

   [1mget_user[0m
           UsersManager.getUser

   [1massign_user[0m
           setUserAccess

[1mAUTHOR[0m
       Jens Gassmann, "<jegade at cpan.org>"

[1mBUGS[0m
       Please report any bugs or feature requests to "bug-piwik-api at
       rt.cpan.org", or through the web interface at
       http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/ReportBug.html?Queue=Piwik-API
       <http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/ReportBug.html?Queue=Piwik-API>.  I will be
       notified, and then you'll automatically be notified of progress on your
       bug as I make changes.

